      • leftBumper

        public edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.buttons.Button leftBumper()
        Returns a Button object representing the left bumper of the gamepad.
        The bumper is the button that is on the front face of the gamepad above the trigger.
        Returns:
        A Button object for the left bumper.

      • rightBumper

      • diamondLeft

        public edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.buttons.Button diamondLeft()
        Returns a Button object for the left button in the diamond group of buttons on the gamepad.
        The diamond group of buttons is the set of four buttons on the right side of the gamepad either labeled 1,2,3,4 or X,Y,B,A.
        Returns:
        A Button object for the left diamond button.

      • getLeftX

        public double getLeftX()
        Returns the current value of the x-axis of the left joystick.
        A value of -1 indicates that the joystick is fully left.
        A value of 1 indicates that the joystick is fully right.
        Returns:
        The current value of the x-axis of the left joystick.

      • getLeftY

        public double getLeftY()
        Returns the current value of the y-axis of the left joystick.
        A value of -1 indicates that the joystick is fully down.
        A value of 1 indicates that the joystick is fully up.
        Returns:
        The current value of the y-axis of the left joystick.
